<div class="row">
  <div class="span8">

    <h1>Your Account</h1>

    <p>You can always get back to this page by clicking your username in the navigation bar.</p>

    <p>You can update your <%= gravatar_tag current_user.avatar_url %> Gravatar on
      <a href="http://www.gravatar.com/">the Gravatar website.</a></p>

    <h2>Setup</h2>

    <h3>Start a trail</h3>

    <p>Pick one or more of the available languages.</p>

    <h3>Install the gem</h3>

    <pre>
      $ gem install exercism
    </pre>

    <h3>Login</h3>

    <p>Your credentials get saved in a config file in your home directory: <kbd>.exercism</kbd>.</p>

    <pre>
      $ exercism login
      Your GitHub username: <%= current_user.username %>
      Your exercism.io API key: <%= current_user.key %>
      What is your exercism exercises project path? (/your/project/path)
    </pre>

    <p>If the path in parentheses is a good project path, just hit enter. It uses the current directory as the default
      suggestion.</p>

    <p>If you mess up your login, you can either edit the config file at <kbd>~/.exercism</kbd> or say
      <kbd>exercism logout</kbd> and then try again.</p>

    <h3>Get the code</h3>

    <pre>
      $ cd projects/exercises # or whatever
      $ exercism fetch
    </pre>

    <h3>Submit the assignment</h3>

    <pre>
      $ exercism submit yourcode.rb
    </pre>

    <h2>Language-specific Setup</h2>

    <h3>Ruby</h3>

    <ul>
      <li>Install ruby. (Should we suggest `ruby-build`? `rvm`?)</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Execute the tests with:</p>

    <pre>
      $ ruby bob_test.rb
    </pre>

    <h3>JavaScript</h3>

    <ul>
      <li>Install <a href="http://nodejs.org/">Node.js</a></li>
      <li>Install <a href="https://github.com/mhevery/jasmine-node">jasmine-node</a></li>
    </ul>

    <pre>
      $ brew install node
      $ npm install jasmine-node -g
    </pre>

    <p>Update the `~/.bash_profile` to include NPM binary files on the PATH:</p>

    <pre>
      $ export PATH=/usr/local/share/npm/bin:$PATH
    </pre>

    <p>Execute the tests with:</p>

    <pre>
      $ jasmine-node bob_test.spec.js
    </pre>

    <h3>Elixir</h3>

    <h4>Installation:</h4>

    <ul>
      <li>
        Homebrew for Mac OS X
        <ul>
          <li>Since Elixir requires Erlang R16B, first call <code>brew tap homebrew/versions</code> and then
            <code>brew install erlang-r16</code></li>
          <li>If you have a previous Erlang version installed, unlink it with <code>brew uninstall erlang</code> and
            link the new one with <code>brew link erlang-r16</code></li>
          <li>Update your homebrew to latest: <code>brew update</code></li>
          <li>Install Elixir: <code>brew install elixir</code></li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>Fedora 17+ and Fedora Rawhide: <code>sudo yum -y install elixir</code></li>
      <li>Arch Linux : Elixir is available on AUR via <code>yaourt -S elixir</code></li>
      <li>Other: Get <a href="http://www.erlang.org/download.html">Erlang R16B</a>, then download a
        <a href="http://elixir-lang.org/packages.html">precompiled package</a></li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Running tests:</h4>

    <pre>
      $ elixir bob_test.exs
    </pre>

  </div>

  <div class="span4">
    <dl>
      <dt>Api key:</dt>
      <dd><%= current_user.key %></dd>
    </dl>

    <% unless unstarted.empty? %>
        <h2>Unstarted Trails</h2>
        <% unstarted.each do |language| %>
            <form action="/user/<%= language %>/start" method="POST">
              <input type="submit" value="start <%= language %>"/>
            </form>
        <% end %>
    <% end %>
  </div>
</div>
